ErrorRatesPowerSetVector - Class in org.platanios.learn.combination.error
A structure that holds the individual error rates of a set of functions, as well as the joint error rates of all possible subsets of those functions.
ErrorRatesPowerSetVector(int, int) - Constructor for class org.platanios.learn.combination.error.ErrorRatesPowerSetVector
Constructs a power set indexed vector, holding the error rates, stored as a one-dimensional array and initializes the values of those error rates to be 0.25 for the individual function error rates and a computed value for the joint error rates assuming that each function's error rate is independent of the rest (this independence assumption is made only for the initialization of those error rates values and has nothing to do with the actual error rates estimation problem).
ErrorRatesPowerSetVector(int, int, double) - Constructor for class org.platanios.learn.combination.error.ErrorRatesPowerSetVector
Constructs a power set indexed vector, holding the error rates, stored as a one-dimensional array and initializes the values of those error rates to be initialValue for the individual function error rates and a computed value for the joint error rates assuming that each function's error rate is independent of the rest (this independence assumption is made only for the initialization of those error rates values and has nothing to do with the actual error rates estimation problem).
ErrorRatesPowerSetVector(int, int, boolean[], boolean[][]) - Constructor for class org.platanios.learn.combination.error.ErrorRatesPowerSetVector
Constructs a power set indexed vector, holding the error rates, stored as a one-dimensional array and initializes the values of those error rates to the sample error rates computed from the available labeled data samples and the outputs of the functions for each data sample.
